S P A T Z, you give yourself too much credit. We knew who you were; it wasn't even original. You've always been death on these threads. Look around you boy, its bound too scare you, look at all the posts. After you have posted other then to respond to your ignorance nobody responds after that and the tread dies.  <br>
What scared you most with the pale horse posting was that you didn't know how to respond, because you really don't understand life, death and the value of those who have had to fight for life. <br>
You see Spatz, its been easy to psychoanalysis you. A Spatzism psychological profile was easy to compile and analysis. That's why you couldn't stay here on this post and had to go to the other sites to spread you sickness. <br>
You're so predictable, that's why Israel would get a response from you. Why LOST INNOCENSE caused you so much pain, because you couldn't identify with what is real in life and you felt left out AGAIN. That's why you need a motherly hand to stroke your ego, and to tell you that everything is going to be all right. All mamas' boys are like that. That's why you still sleep with a night light on. <br>
Since the War, you've been running away from the real meaning of life. But, you're also a parasite; we called them leeches in Nam. You feed upon and regurgitate the misery of others in order to make yourself feel important. To make yourself feel needed and to justify your existence or self worth, you do it to appease the nagging question in your mind, that you have been struggling with all your life. Am I a coward? I bet you ask yourself that everyday. Why you try to make friends with Vets, but can't stand to have a serious dialog with those that challenge your weak heart.  Like the cowardly Lion in the Wizard of Oz, you think a medal will give you a brave heart and settle your need for acceptance. <br>
It's called PCOS, Post Conscientious Objector Syndrome. One day I'll post the study made on that subject, since it stands for hiding behind useless memories and ideals. It means using them as shields of justification for your actions during the war. It means having to deal with the reality of life without a joint, drugs and  a real purpose in life.<br>
Meanwhile spatz, keep fighting that little boy inside you that is a wannabe be warrior. That's why  you get so much enjoyment out of watching a Dirty Harry movies and owning big guns. <br>
&quot;I stood in a trench, once upon a time, in 1967, with an Uzi in my hands, TREMBLING, looking out at Jordan.&quot; <br>
Gosh, sparry,trembling and standing in a real trench line, WOW, and you touched a real Uzi; good thing the Israeli soldier took out the magazine so that it wasn't loaded. You could have shot yourself.  Spatz Israel and you do not compute, they have no place in trench lines for conscientious objectors.<br>
I would have loved to have had you ride along with me in Watts and Southeast LA, especially during pursuits and hot shots, you would have defecated and peed all over yourself on the midnight shift. I totaled out nine patrol cars chasing after goonies like you that cried over a simple parking ticket, and no, spatz, I did not take a medical or stress pension to get out of the system like your cop friends. <br>
You've never answered my questions; simple questions that I honestly want to know the answers to, like,<br>
How does it feel to be a coward? A homosexual? What do you tell your sons, when they ask what did you do during the war daddy? <br>

